@page "/"

<PageTitle>WeatherApp</PageTitle>

<MudContainer MaxWidth="MaxWidth.Medium" Class="mt-8">
    <MudPaper Class="pa-6 rounded-xl" Elevation="4">
        <MudText Typo="Typo.h2" Class="mb-2">
            WeatherApp
        </MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.h5" Color="Color.Primary" Class="mb-4">
            By Ryan Wlock
        </MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-4">
            WeatherApp is a weather dashboard built with Blazor and MudBlazor that integrates with the National Weather Service API. 
            It allows users to search weather zones and stations by state and location, 
            then view detailed daily and hourly forecasts through an intuitive dashboard.
        </MudText>

        <MudDivider Class="my-4" />

        <MudText Typo="Typo.h5" Class="mb-3">
            How to Use WeatherApp
        </MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-2">
            1. Click the <strong>Weather</strong> tab in the navigation header.
        </MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-2">
            2. Enter a U.S. state abbreviation such as <strong>CO</strong>, <strong>TX</strong>, or <strong>CA</strong>.
        </MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-2">
            3. Select a forecast zone, then choose a weather station.
        </MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1">
            4. Explore the selected location’s weather, including a 7-day forecast and a detailed 24-hour forecast.
        </MudText>
    </MudPaper>
</MudContainer>